{
  "stem": "22869.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my mother was also coming from a very, very religious family.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in general, we were very observant at home, daily services, and were always, you know, had to attend to, under strict rules.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And of course, when we were little, we had to have these services in class.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I would say the house was kept very, very strictly, even to my today's way of thinking, in an orthodox manner.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There were no deviations whatsoever to-- from-- from religion.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And it wasn't really forced upon you.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You-- you grew up with it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I mean, that was our way of living.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Examples as what?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, let's put it this way.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There's without any doubt that everything in the house was kosher, because we did not enjoy the-- the pleasantries that we can enjoy today, as far as the bounty full of foods and so forth.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we lived on a minimum.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But nobody went hungry to bed.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "As far as the strictness of the religion was that you had very, very little-- a minimum time-- in the day for playing.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And most of it was pushed by my father, especially, towards Jewish studies, to extents that, in today's world, would be considered very, very extreme.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Even in the most extreme neighborhoods, it would be considered-- this was very fanatic to-- I give you an example.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Like when I had a free minute, I had to go-- instead of playing-- I had to go to Hebrew school for Hebrew studies, and so did my brothers.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My father was-- at last, when we left home, at least-- he was a wine merchant.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were making wine wholesales, selling it wholesale and retail.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Kosher wine and non-kosher wine.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I had-- I had-- altogether, we were seven-- two sisters, five brothers.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
